review:
First and foremost, Dr.  Vivekananda Reddy made me feel welcome and comfortable throughout the visit, addressing all my needs with care and professionalism.

His guidance and procedures were exceptional. After struggling with a tooth infection for over a year, it was finally cured within a week following his treatment.
Doctor was patient and helful.given time to listen the issue and  explained medicines  properly and with patience

Ok, so I had this small pain near my upper molar & I could notice some cavity is started. I didn't want it to spread and searched for doctors on Practo. I was looking for someone who is a surgeon and experts in dental implants; as I had them done and explaining my problem would be easier. 
On visiting him, it was diagnosed that my wisdom tooth is causing pain. The tooth with the cavity was a separate issue. He suggested removing it as the gum holding it was loose and no point in doing the RCT. 

I wasn't prepared for the same and I was sort of surprised. I asked him if I could talk to my wife and make a decision. I had to do it, but talking to her would put me at ease and be ready with the tooth removal. 

Took the decision, he said it would be painless. I got two injections, at the molar and teeth that required the cavity to be fixed. 

Surprisingly for the first time ever I didn't feel any pain (except of course the injection part). 

I was done in less than 10-15 mins. 1 filling and 1 removal.
